00076 // Verify that the primitive types have the correct size.  The C
00077 // standard indicates that sizeof() returns units of char, so we must
00078 // also verify that a char is 8 bits. If any of these asserts fail, the
00079 // app would not be conforming to the protocol, and changes would be needed.
00080 _compiler_assert( CHAR_BIT          == 8, _FMI_H_ );
00081 _compiler_assert( sizeof( boolean ) == 1, _FMI_H_ );
00082 _compiler_assert( sizeof( uint8 )   == 1, _FMI_H_ );
00083 _compiler_assert( sizeof( sint8 )   == 1, _FMI_H_ );
00084 _compiler_assert( sizeof( uint16 )  == 2, _FMI_H_ );
00085 _compiler_assert( sizeof( sint16 )  == 2, _FMI_H_ );
00086 _compiler_assert( sizeof( uint32 )  == 4, _FMI_H_ );
00087 _compiler_assert( sizeof( sint32 )  == 4, _FMI_H_ );
00088 _compiler_assert( sizeof( float32 ) == 4, _FMI_H_ );
00089 _compiler_assert( sizeof( float64 ) == 8, _FMI_H_ );
